Today I worked on designing and integrating a chatbot module into the Zenon CropTrial system to automate the e-way bill generation process. The idea is that once customer details, products, and transaction data are entered into the system, the chatbot will intelligently process this information and generate the required e-way bill without manual intervention. I focused on defining the workflow, mapping the required fields, and understanding how the chatbot can interact with existing modules like customers, inventory, and orders. Initial implementation involved structuring the data flow and identifying triggers for automatic bill creation. This approach will significantly reduce manual effort and improve accuracy in generating e-way bills within the system.
